kes sense to simulate skip with the starting base. It seems like the next class test might include the method name and return the class only, which is okay. \\n\\nThe helper in `akka.testkit.bridge` has package-private access to `akka.testkit.TestKitUtils`, which is fine. The top-level class needs to be public, and the TestKitUtilsTest is public too. I wonder if I can avoid using a helper by placing the entire package in `akka.testkit.bridge`, but I know there are rules about keeping tests outside library packages. So, it looks like using a helper is a compromise I have to make.\\n\\n**Clarifying package syntax in Scala 3**\\n\\nI’m figuring out the package syntax in Scala 3. It looks like I can declare a package like `package akka.testkit.bridge` at the top of the file, which applies to the entire file. However, if I want multiple packages, I should use braces, such as:\\n\\n```\\npackage akka.testkit.bridge {\\n   ...\\n}\\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_testkit_3 {\\n   ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis structure is supported in Scala 3. I’ll also need to ensure that my imports are inside the package braces. Time to write the file!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0de03878d8e79384016a28556fb03881948beebddf56c33d0d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqKFWOF4mv0eml0FEh-7cjin6j9nHDNXu1IQqLhe57Jqs17_7IP-HQfTKMlBGYUCkKK4orPV499LrgwZLXP6OiVFfairMEPWFHAgLCHTZ7LQnecrGyorssDYqLxIUJZNqtxxcQtsA4RtXtjs5_GR_YEOXgmwjMzD0EEfSDSVe9Ve7_mDgno1d-DBePN0KYF0Wi88ZEapn51wK5EV8g7PqouB1lJUy3B1QnnwfbdiTcIR1iqUXchbfyFQmckb5qwh8qw-99qCFex0LL8_yuq_IejUevZ4CWpAYhfJ7bCAYLrFUDfCv1WvnjQaXzJsgfjBVOKxj3Gv-dVRrxct26N9ENImx_TPyyct6qYPm-ZaOZwvPAH44INJyM3Gp9QqUh4sA2dfYrVnWHoWiSKFkEMVgSkn_QyjFggCLRqv3mD0gPs6vd5tzd6o2PQWjY0b7iKJBD0iOzovn6jYEOokalotAXZFgYgVkuKafc8_V2KUigAKh4U9njFjLauNnvzuU1W1qAouMyGw1NzOozrUXooaSgjRzyg7qEIwuIqXXiDfr3viA2OIxXOwZoS6lyVLcaAuxDKgpokFymh3o9bKLzzilzNsZN6dCZ-f7oM7uvJMoGCSSumf0wTqfgfHyBhFTQTjmmvm5UEqTccX1JUCC_KGjE_n8KHxN